"tag\" or just \"tag\" for short is often used in place of \"802.1q_ VLAN "
"header\". QinQ allows multiple VLAN tags in an Ethernet frame; together "
"these tags constitute a tag stack. When used in the context of an "
"Ethernet frame, a QinQ frame is a frame that has 2 VLAN 802.1q_ headers "
"(double-tagged)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_include/interface-vlan-8021ad.txt:22
