#: ../../configuration/nat/nat44.rst:43
msgid ""
"If an ISP deploys a :abbr:`CGN (Carrier-grade NAT)`, and uses :rfc:`1918`"
" address space to number customer gateways, the risk of address "
"collision, and therefore routing failures, arises when the customer "
"network already uses an :rfc:`1918` address space."
